        >, co-located with the 21st International Conference of the Italian
        Association for Artifical Intelligence (AI*IA 2022), 2022, Unversità
        degli Studi di Udine, Udine. Oral Presentation <a
          class="badge badge-secondary mx-2 ml-0 my-1"
          href="/pdfs/slide_nl4ai_2022.pdf">Check out the Slides</a
        >
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">
      Partecipations in Research Schools and Workshops
    </div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li class="text-accent">
      <span class="text-primary-content">
        <b>Lectures on Computational Linguistics 2025</b>, June 18-20 2025,
        Catholic University of the Sacred Heart, Milan;
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="text-accent">
      <span class="text-primary-content">
        <b>Learning over Time (LoT),</b> Doctoral Spring School, March 24-27 2025,
        Certosa di Pontignano, Siena;
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="text-accent">
      <span class="text-primary-content">
        <b>Lectures on Computational Linguistics 2023</b>, May 29-31 2023,
        University of Pisa, Pisa;
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="text-accent">
      <span class="text-primary-content">
        <b>Lectures on Computational Linguistics 2022</b>, June 8-10 2022,
        Università degli Studi di Napoli "L'Orientale", Napoli;
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="text-accent">
      <span class="text-primary-content">
        <b>PyCon Italia 2022</b>, June 2-5 2022, Grand Hotel Mediterraneo,
